          "text": "## Commit 3: M15.4 — orchestrator subpackage\n\nM15.4 says: create `pkg/distill/internal/orchestrator/` that bridges public Options → internal pipeline. Per the DoD, M15.2 builds on top of this, so landing it first makes the M15.2 commit thinner and properly enforces the layering. Let me design the orchestrator's API.\n\nIt needs to:\n1. Take a public `Options` (from `pkg/distill`) plus the io.Reader and io.Writer.\n2. Resolve format (detect or explicit).\n3. Wire envelope stripping.\n4. Build the pipeline.\n5. Return: Event channel, the Sink (so Distill can read EventsEmitted post-run), the BudgetCounters, the LineCounter, and a Run function the caller invokes.\n\nOr simpler: provide a single `New(ctx, opts, r) (*Run, error)` that captures all state, and a `Run.Start()` returning the channel, and a `Run.Wait()` returning the Summary.\n\nLet me make this clean and testable:",
