er, unknown Output,\nunknown Format, unknown StripEnvelope — return synchronously from\n`Distill` before any goroutine starts. The orchestrator's internal\nsentinels are remapped onto public sentinels so callers use\n`errors.Is(err, distill.ErrNilWriter)` without importing the\ninternal package.\n\n`ExitCodeFromSummary(*Summary) int` reproduces the CLI's 0/1/2/3\ncontract so a binary built on the library can replicate the exit\nsemantics. The four constants `ExitOK`, `ExitNoEvents`,\n`ExitError`, `ExitPartial` are pinned to their numeric values by\n`TestExitCodeConstants_StableValues` so a downstream bash\nconsumer's `[[ $? -eq 3 ]]` check survives refactoring.\n\nLayering is enforced by two integration tests:\n`TestPublicAPI_NoLeakedInternalImports` parses every `.go` file\ndirectly under `pkg/distill/` and asserts every `internal/*`\nimport is either a documented type-alias target\n(`internal/event`, `internal/formats`) or a side-effect import\nfor registry registration; `TestPublicAPI_OrchestratorIsPrivate`\nconfirms the orchestrator sits under `pkg/distill/internal/` so\nGo's standard visibility rule protects it.\n\n## Docs touched\n\n- `pkg/distill/distill.go`: package godoc rewritten; \"M14\" stub\n  references replaced with the shipped M15 surface description.\n  Godoc on `Distill`, the four sentinel errors, every helper.\n- `pkg/distill/options.go`: godoc on every field of `Options`,\n  `OutputFormat`, `Summary`, including the `Wait` / `Done`\n  timing contract and the `ForcedDrops` nil-safe contract.\n- `pkg/distill/exitcode.go`: godoc on `ExitCodeFromSummary` and\n  the four exit-code constants.\n- `docs/library-api.md`: new full reference (~270 lines) covering\n  consumption patterns, Summary timing, error model, exit-code\n  mapping, config-files non-feature, `os/exec` migration guide,\n  versioning, format-set customisation.\n- `README.md`: \"Library use\" subsection rewritten as \"Embedding\n  in Go\" with a six-line worked example and a cross-link.\n- `skills/distill-ai/SKILL.md`: new \"Embedding in Go (library\n  use)\" section so agents producing Go code know when to import\n  rather than shell out.\n- `ARCHITECTURE.md`: § Library API rewritten to describe the\n  shipped surface and the orchestrator layering.\n- `CHANGELOG.md`: per-sub-item entries under `[Unreleased]`.\n- `TODO.md`: M15 sub-items ticked; M17 expanded; scoping\n  preamble updated.\n\n## Tests added\n\n`pkg/distill/`:\n\n- `TestOptions_OutputFormatStringers`, `TestOptions_DefaultsAreSafe`\n  — pin the zero-value defaults and constant stringers.\n- `TestOptions_SummaryFieldsMatchSchema` — drift guard between\n  the Go `Summary` struct and SCHEMA.md's summary table; both\n  directions.\n- `TestSummary_ForcedDrops*` — four arms (drops, truncations,\n  clean run, nil receiver).\n- `TestDistill_PipeToText`, `TestDistill_PipeToJSON`,\n  `TestDistill_PipeToJSONStreaming` — exercise every Output arm.\n- `TestDistill_ExplicitFormatBeatsAutodetect`,\n  `TestDistill_AutodetectFallsBackToGeneric`,\n  `TestDistill_StrictReturnsErrorOnLowConfidence` — format-\n  resolution and Strict mode.\n- `TestDistill_NilWriterErrors`, `TestDistill_UnknownTokenizerErrors`,\n  `TestDistill_UnknownFormatErrors`, `TestDistill_UnknownOutputErrors`\n  — each sentinel-error arm.\n- `TestDistill_SummaryReflectsCounters` — Summary and JSON\n  trailer agree on numbers.\n- `TestDistill_StreamingBeforeEOF` — `slowReader` proves the\n  channel emits Events before EOF.\n- `TestDistill_ContextCancellationClosesChannel` — channel\n  closes within 2s of `cancel()`.\n- `TestDistill_NoGoroutineLeak` — 20 cancelled iterations,\n  goroutine count returns to baseline.\n- `TestDistill_DeterministicForFixedInput` — same input twice\n  → byte-equal output AND matching Summary.\n- `TestDistill_EventChannelDeliversEvents` — channel count\n  matches `Summary.EventsEmitted`.\n- `TestExitCodeFromSummary_*` (six) — every documented arm\n  including nil receiver and the ExitPartial > ExitNoEvents\n  precedence rule.\n- Five `ExampleDistill_*` runnable godoc examples (text, JSON\n  batch, JSON streaming, explicit format, context cancellation)\n  with `// Output:` assertions.\n\n`pkg/distill/internal/orchestrator/`:\n\n- Twelve unit tests covering every sentinel error, the end-to-end\n  gotest path, explicit format vs autodetect, zero-events exit-\n  code mapping, context cancellation, ndjson output, markdown\n  fence-lang, MinSeverity propagation into ParseOpts.\n- `TestOrchestrator_EventChannelExposesEvents` — channel sees\n  the same count as `Summary.EventsEmitted`.\n\n`test/integration/`:\n\n- `TestPublicAPI_NoLeakedInternalImports` — parses every `.go`\n  file directly under `pkg/distill/` and asserts the import\n  contract.\n- `TestPublicAPI_OrchestratorIsPrivate` — confirms the\n  orchestrator path sits under `pkg/distill/internal/`.\n\nAll tests pass under `-race`.\n\n## Per-commit detail\n\nPRHEAD\ncat /var/folders/_4/hgrfrlss2ql9mmz8rb1_psh00000gn/T/opencode/pr/commits-html.txt >> /var/folders/_4/hgrfrlss2ql9mmz8rb1_psh00000gn/T/opencode/pr/body.md\nwc -l /var/folders/_4/hgrfrlss2ql9mmz8rb1_psh00000gn/T/opencode/pr/body.md",
